<item>
            <title>[FLINK-14818] StreamNetworkBenchmarkEnvironment incorrectly setups a receiving InputGate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14818</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In network benchmark (for example 1000 channels benchmark with 4 record writers) &lt;tt&gt;StreamNetworkBenchmarkEnvironment#createInputGate&lt;/tt&gt; creates 1000 input gates with 4 input channels each, which doesn&apos;t make much sense. I would expect either having 4 receivers with single input gate with 1000 channels each, or a single receiver with 4 input gates, with 1000 channels each.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
